@NODE faq "Frequently Asked Questions"

Frequently Asked Questions

Q: In mails mode, it says "Length: xxx (yyy)" in the header.  
   What does it mean?
A: xxx = the number of lines in the mail, yyy = the size in Kb

Q: When I use the optimize function, a lot of *.bak files are created. 
   Is it safe to remove these?
A: Yes, you can remove them.  It might be wise to keep them as a backup of
   your database, though.

Q: I have some problems with MiniMail; whom should I ask?
A: You should always ask me first.  If it turns out to be a bug in MiniMail,
   I'll forward the information to Pelle Claesson.

Q: How do I check MiniMail's integrity?
A: Simply write "PGP MiniMail" from a shell, after adding my public key to
   your keyring.  (Feel free to ask me for my public key, if you don't trust
   the one in the documentation.)

Q: Why would people never dream of do the things they dream of doing?
A: --- :)

@ENDNODE

